cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.IT, cs.DC 

The paper deals with a vulnerability in Wi-Fi networks, which is a subfield of network security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the feasibility of the attack through experiments, simulations, and theoretical analysis, which falls under the subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also models the network as a dynamical system, which could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.IT (Information Theory). Finally, the paper discusses the impact of the attack on the entire network, which could be categorized under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
